Hi there <@U02227D27V3>,
I've finished the course and submit my practicum.
I tried following the requirements as closely as possible. Since there was no instruction on merging the `working-branch` to `main` , I didn't do so. I thought the examiner would check the branch.

I just learned that I failed the practicum because the `main` branch if the exact copy of the fork but my work is all in the `working-branch`.

Maybe I'm being silly, but might be a good idea to add this to the requirements :slightly_smiling_face:

Anyway, I've merged it to main and resubmit again.
:crossed_fingers:
Hello <@U02DYFPJH4J>, thank you for the feedback. I will add a note in the requirements to re-merge the branches.
